## Section 2: Agent Lifecycle & Nix Environment Model

**Agent profiles as Nix expressions:**

```nix
# forge-profiles/default.nix
{ forgeLib, ... }:
{
  base = forgeLib.mkAgent {
    name = "base";
    tools = [ "git" "gh" "ripgrep" "fd" ];
    mcp-servers = [];
    secrets = [];
    resources = { cpu = 1; memory = "2Gi"; };
    permissions = {
      repo = "read-write";
      network = [];  # no egress by default
      spawn = { max-children = 5; require-approval-after = 3; };
    };
  };

  security-reviewer = forgeLib.mkAgent {
    name = "security-reviewer";
    inherit (base) tools;
    tools = base.tools ++ [ "semgrep" "trivy" "bandit" ];
    mcp-servers = [ "github" ];
    secrets = [ "GITHUB_TOKEN" ];
    resources = { cpu = 2; memory = "4Gi"; };
    permissions = {
      repo = "read-only";
      network = [ "api.github.com" "*.semgrep.dev" ];
      spawn = { max-children = 0; };  # leaf agent, can't spawn
    };
  };

  implementer = forgeLib.mkAgent {
    name = "implementer";
    tools = base.tools ++ [ "cargo" "rustc" "nodejs" "npm" ];
    mcp-servers = [ "filesystem" "github" ];
    secrets = [ "GITHUB_TOKEN" "NPM_TOKEN" ];
    resources = { cpu = 4; memory = "8Gi"; };
    permissions = {
      repo = "read-write";
      network = [ "registry.npmjs.org" "crates.io" ];
      spawn = { max-children = 10; require-approval-after = 5; };
    };
  };
}
```

**`forgeLib.mkAgent` produces a structured attrset:**

```nix
# forgeLib/mkAgent.nix
{ name, tools, mcp-servers, secrets, resources, permissions }:
{
  # Nix derivation: the materialized environment
  env = pkgs.buildEnv {
    name = "forge-agent-${name}";
    paths = map (t: pkgs.${t}) tools;
  };

  # Capability manifest (pure data, no derivation)
  manifest = {
    inherit name secrets resources permissions mcp-servers;
    toolPaths = map (t: "${pkgs.${t}}/bin") tools;
  };
}
```

**Agent lifecycle managed by the daemon:**

```
1. SPAWN REQUEST
   Primary agent вҶ’ daemon: "spawn security-reviewer for repo X"
                           (Nix profile name + runtime overrides)

2. NIX EVALUATION
   Daemon runs: nix eval .#profiles.security-reviewer.manifest
   вҶ’ Returns capability manifest (pure JSON, no build yet)
   вҶ’ Cached after first eval per profile

3. APPROVAL GATE
   Daemon checks policy:
   в”ңв”Җ Total agent count < spawn cap? вҶ’ continue
   в”ңв”Җ Total agent count вүҘ cap? вҶ’ request parent approval
   в”ңв”Җ Secrets requested? вҶ’ check vault ACL
   в”ңв”Җ Network egress requested? вҶ’ check allowlist policy
   в””в”Җ All clear вҶ’ proceed to materialization

4. MATERIALIZATION
   Daemon runs: nix build .#profiles.security-reviewer.env
   вҶ’ Produces /nix/store/...-forge-agent-security-reviewer/
   вҶ’ Cached after first build (subsequent spawns are instant)

5. NAMESPACE CREATION
   Daemon invokes bubblewrap:
   bwrap \
     --ro-bind /nix/store /nix/store \          # Nix env (read-only)
     --bind /workspace/repo-x /workspace \       # Shared workspace
     --bind /run/forge/agent-$ID /run/forge \    # UDS for services
     --dev /dev \
     --proc /proc \
     --unshare-pid \                             # PID namespace
     --die-with-parent \                         # Clean up on daemon crash
     --new-session \
     -- claude --print --output-format stream-json

6. SERVICE BINDING
   Daemon creates per-agent UDS endpoints:
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/auth.sock      вҶ’ Auth proxy
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/cache.sock     вҶ’ Cache service
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/mcp.sock       вҶ’ MCP router (only configured servers)
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/vault.sock     вҶ’ Key vault (only approved secrets)
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/bus.sock       вҶ’ Message bus
   /run/forge/agent-$ID/spawn.sock     вҶ’ Spawn API (for sub-agent requests)

7. RUNNING
   Agent executes with:
   - PATH pointing to Nix-provided tools only
   - Environment variables for service socket paths
   - cgroup limits enforcing CPU/memory from manifest
   - Network namespace with only allowed egress (via slirp4netns or --unshare-net)

8. TERMINATION
   On completion/timeout/kill:
   - Daemon reaps process
   - Flushes agent logs to persistence
   - Releases cgroup resources
   - Removes UDS endpoints
   - Notifies parent via message bus
   - Decrements spawn counter
```

**macOS fallback:** On macOS (no Linux namespaces), the daemon uses Docker instead of bubblewrap. The `AgentRuntime` trait abstracts this:

```rust
#[async_trait]
trait AgentRuntime: Send + Sync {
    async fn spawn(&self, manifest: AgentManifest, workspace: &Path) -> Result<AgentHandle>;
    async fn kill(&self, handle: &AgentHandle) -> Result<()>;
    async fn status(&self, handle: &AgentHandle) -> Result<AgentStatus>;
}

struct BwrapRuntime { /* Linux namespace impl */ }
struct DockerRuntime { /* Docker/bollard impl */ }
```

**Spawn approval model:**

```
permissions.spawn = {
  max-children = 10;          # hard cap, never exceeded
  require-approval-after = 5; # soft cap, parent asked after this
};
```

- Agents 1вҖ“5: auto-approved, parent notified
- Agents 6вҖ“10: parent must explicitly approve each spawn
- Agent 11+: denied, parent gets rejection with reason

